    "explanation": "\n<p>$K_p$ and $K_c$ are related as per the following formula:</p>\n\n<p>$$ K_p=K_c(R T)^{\\Delta n(g)} $$</p>\n<p>For the given equation:</p>\n<p>$$ \\Delta n_{(g)}=[2 \\text { due to } C+3 \\text { due to } D]-[1 \\text { due to } A+2 \\text { due to } B]=5-3=2 $$</p>\n<p>Putting $\\Delta n_{(g)}=2$,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{gathered} K_p=K_c(R T)^2 \\\\ \\frac{K_p}{K_c}=(R T)^2 \\\\ \\Rightarrow \\frac{K_p}{K_c} \\propto T^2 \\end{gathered} $$</p>",
